Data type: Data type is defined as what type of data to store in the variable
there are 5 types of data types available in java script:
1) Number Datatype
2) String Datatype
3) Boolean Datatype
4) Regular Datatype
5) Arrays

Number Data type:
 var x = 36; //  x stores the decimal number value. so var is number data type
 var x= 36.5; // y stores the floating number value
 
 String Data type :
 
 strings are stored in variable using single or double quotes
 
 examlple
        var name="java script";
        documnt.write("hello" + name ); // prints hello java script
        
 Boolean Data type: only two value true or false
        var x= true; // its not string if it is string we mention ""
        
 Regular expression:
                var x= 38;
                var y= 55;
                var z= x + y ; // this is regular expression
                doument.write(z);
               
 Array: 
 An array is a special variable, which can hold more than one value at a time.
If you have a list of items (a list of car names, for example), storing the cars in single variables could look like this
var car1 = "Saab";
var car2 = "Volvo";
var car3 = "BMW";

 now its okay if you have 100 statements the code is more complexe seo use arrays it stores many values at a time with same data type
 array index start from 0 to n-1;
 creating an array 
 var array_name = [item1, item2, ...];    
 var cars =["saab", "volvo", "" BMW]; 
 doxument.write(cars[0]); // accessing element in array 
